SUMMARY:PROJECT HAIL MARY   -  IMAX   -   Followed by a drink or a bite
DESCRIPTION:Toronto Movies & Social Group - Celebrating 14 Years!\n**Plot*
 * **summary**: Science teacher Ryland Grace (Ryan Gosling) wakes up on a s
 paceship light years from home with no recollection of who he is or how he
  got there. As his memory returns\, he begins to uncover his mission: solv
 e the riddle of the mysterious substance causing the sun to die out. He mu
 st call on his scientific knowledge and unorthodox ideas to save everythin
 g on Earth from extinction... but an unexpected friendship means he may no
 t have to do it alone.\n\nTrailer\\*\\*: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P
 0XN3-n-2Lo\n\n**Time the Meetup group will meet at:** **6:45pm**...Please 
 **check in** **with** **me** ***by 6:50pm***\, **as we will go into the th
 eatre at that time.**\n\n**Time the movie STARTS:** ***7:00pm***\n\n**Movi
 e Running Time:** *2hr 36min*\n\n**Meetup Spot:** Bottom of the steps to I
 ndigo - Directly across from Cineplex.\n\n**How to Find the Theatre:** Sec
 ond floor of the Yonge Eglinton Centre - next to Yonge St.\n\n**Where I wi
 ll be sitting:** I will be in ROW "G" SEAT "G6'\n\n**Click here to go to t
 he website to buy your ticket:** [https://www.cineplex.com/](https://www.c
 ineplex.com/)\n\n**After the Movie:** We will reconvene by the steps leadi
 ng to INDIGO\, and talk about the meaningful scenes in the movie. Then\, f
 or those who answered YES to the question\, we will go into the Pickle Bar
 rel for a drink or a bite.\n\n**PLEASE NOTE:** Ticket must be bought befor
 e signing up. You will be asked where you will be sitting. Seating is very
  limited.\n*Don't forget to join Cineplex's new MOIVE CLUB for those that 
 love movies and discounts* - [https://www.cineplex.com/cineclub](https://w
 ww.cineplex.com/cineclub)\n\n**NOTE:** All movies are subject to change\, 
 I will always try for the best time\, and to see a movie in 2D (some movie
 s are a must in 3D) for the best price. \\*\\*\\*Also\, please keep an eye
  out for any changes in venue or movie times.\n**I look forward to seeing 
 you there!!**\n\n**THIS GROUP IS OPEN TO THOSE WHO WANT TO BE SOCIAL\, MAK
 E FRIENDS\, WHO ARE SINGLE OR NOT SINGLE. WE ALSO HAVE LOTS OF OTHER EVENT
 S LIKE\, MOVIES\, WALKS\, HIKES\, ARTS & CULTURE AND RESTAURANTS. WE LOVE 
 TO SUPPORT MEMEBERS TO SOCIALIZE AND TO FORM LONG LASTING FRIENDSHIPS.**\n
 \n**Toronto Movies and Social Group: Policy**\n\nPlease do not use your ce
 llphone\, talk\, or otherwise disrupt the enjoyment of others around you\,
  once the movie starts. Any complaints will be dealt with first as a warni
 ng\, then subsequent removal from the group on repeated complaints.\n\n**R
 ules:** [Click Here!](https://www.meetup.com/toronto-movies-and-social-gro
 up/events/293241263/)\n**Getting The Best Out Of Meet:** [Click Here!](htt
 ps://www.meetup.com/toronto-movies-and-social-group/events/293241269/)\n\n
 Don't Forget to join our email list (Meetup does not send out emails to\ne
 veryone in a group) to get our weekly news later about upcoming events: [h
 ttp://eepurl.com/hKt76f](http://eepurl.com/hKt76f)\n\nFacebook group @ [ht
 tp://www.facebook.com/groups/502945113062739/](http://www.facebook.com/gro
 ups/502945113062739/)\n\n**Scene card:** A Scene card helps you to collect
  movie points at Cineplex movie theatres. After 1000 points or 10 movies y
 our 11th movie is free. If you love to see movies then this is a must have
  card. Go to - [https://www.scene.ca](https://www.scene.ca/) to get your c
 ard today\n\nMathew is the organizer for this meetup. If you need to conta
 ct him\, please post a message on the wall\, or email him torontomoviesand
 outings@[hotmail.com](http://hotmail.com/)
