SUMMARY:🥖🏛️ ST. LAWRENCE MARKET WALK & LUNCH 🏛️🥖
DESCRIPTION:Toronto Movies & Social Group - Celebrating 14 Years!\n🥖
 🏛️ ST. LAWRENCE MARKET WALK & LUNCH 🏛️🥖\nHistory\, Hallways &
  Some of the Best Food in Canada\n\nIf you want to understand Toronto\, yo
 u don’t start with the skyline.\nYou start with **St. Lawrence Market**.
 \n\nWidely considered one of the most beloved markets in Canada\, St. Lawr
 ence Market isn’t just a place to grab lunch — it’s woven into the f
 oundation of the city itself. The original market dates back to the early 
 1800s and was one of the first public gathering spaces in what would becom
 e Toronto. Markets were where the city happened — where food was sold\, 
 announcements were made\, and community life unfolded.\nFun fact? The buil
 ding complex has worn many hats over the years. The area once housed Toron
 to’s first City Hall — and yes\, even a jail. Imagine that: politician
 s upstairs\, prisoners downstairs\, and fresh produce somewhere in between
 . Only in early Toronto.\n\nToday\, it remains one of the most celebrated 
 food markets in the country — a place where old-school butchers\, fishmo
 ngers\, bakers\, cheesemakers\, and global food vendors operate side by si
 de. It’s lively\, layered\, and delicious.\nAnd we’re going to experie
 nce it together.\n\n👉 **Don’t forget to join our WhatsApp group** –
  [CLICK HERE!](https://chat.whatsapp.com/H59mSCbsAi018gYANrKAnc?mode=ac_t)
 \n\n***\n\n🚶‍♂️ The Walk There\n\nWe’ll begin at the subway sta
 tion and walk down Broadview\, making our way along Queen East\, over to K
 ing\, and eventually down to Front Street.\n\nIt’s a relaxed urban walk 
 — a chance to chat\, stretch our legs\, and build a little anticipation 
 before the feast.\nPlease only sign up if you’re comfortable walking in 
 rain or colder weather. This event runs unless conditions are extreme.\n\n
 ***\n\n🥟 The Food Plan\n\nOnce we arrive\, we’ll explore both the caf
 é area and the main food market.\n\nExpect options like:\n🥪 Peameal ba
 con sandwiches\n🧀 Local Ontario cheeses\n🥐 Fresh pastries\n🦞 Seaf
 ood counters\n🌮 International eats\n🍁 Maple treats\nDon’t forget t
 o bring some cash — a few vendors are still old-school and cash-only.\n\
 nThe plan: grab whatever calls your name and then find a table to sit and 
 eat together. No pressure\, no fixed menu — just good food and good comp
 any.\n\n***\n\n🧢 Meetup Details\n📍 Meetup Location: Right outside th
 e subway station\n🫎 I’ll be wearing my Moose Hat\n⏰ Meetup Time: 11
 :00 AM\n❗ We will only wait 5 minutes\nEnd Stop: Front & Lower Jarvis\nY
 ou’re welcome to leave at any time.\n\n***\n\n🎟️ **Meetup Fee:** $5
  cash in person **or** e-transfer to\n📧 \\*\\*[mathewmaclean@hotmail.co
 m**](http://mathewmaclean@hotmail.com%2A%2A/)\nThis fee helps support the 
 group and allows us to keep hosting events like this. Thank you for suppor
 ting community! 💖\n\n***\n\n🌈 Who Is This For?\nThis group is open t
 o anyone who wants to be social and make friends — whether single or not
 .\nWe also host:\n🎬 Movies\n🚶 Walks & hikes\n🎭 Arts & culture out
 ings\n🍽️ Restaurant gatherings\nThere’s always something happening.
 \nAnd remember — you can just show up on the day if you’re unsure abou
 t your schedule.\n\n***\n\n⚠️ A Gentle Reminder\nSometimes life happen
 s and plans shift — please keep an eye out for updates in case of cancel
 lation.\n\n***\n\n👤 Organizer: Mathew\nQuestions? Post on the event wal
 l or email\n📧 torontomoviesandoutings@hotmail.com\n\nCome for the histo
 ry.\nStay for the food.\nLeave understanding Toronto just a little bit bet
 ter — and probably carrying a pastry for later.\nThere’s something mag
 ical about eating in a place where the city has been gathering for over 20
 0 years.\n\nLet’s go taste it. 🥖✨
